---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words With Double T — BUTTERFLY, KITTEN, BUTTER, BOTTLE" description="Top double-T Scrabble words: BUTTERFLY (17pts), KITTEN (10pts), BUTTER (8pts), BOTTLE (8pts). Master TT patterns for high-scoring plays and bingos." keywords="scrabble double t words, butterfly scrabble, kitten scrabble, butter scrabble, bottle scrabble, double t strategy, tt words scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words With Double T — BUTTERFLY, KITTEN, BUTTER, BOTTLE","description":"Master double-T words in Scrabble: BUTTERFLY, KITTEN, BUTTER, BOTTLE with TT pattern strategy for scoring.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-t"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the highest-scoring double-T words in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"BUTTERFLY scores 17 points (plus 50-point bingo bonus for 9 letters used with blanks), KITTEN scores 10 points, and BUTTER and BOTTLE each score 8 points. The Y in BUTTERFLY adds 4 points while the B and F add 7 combined."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many T tiles are in a Scrabble bag?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"There are 6 T tiles in a standard Scrabble bag, each worth 1 point. T is one of the most common consonants, making double-T draws fairly frequent — roughly 1 in 4 racks contain at least two T's."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What patterns help spot double-T words?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Look for -UTTER (BUTTER, GUTTER, NUTTER), -OTTEN (ROTTEN, GOTTEN), -ITTEN (KITTEN, MITTEN, BITTEN), -ATTLE (BATTLE, RATTLE, CATTLE), and -OTTLE (BOTTLE, MOTTLE, DOTTLE). These suffixes combine with many starting consonants."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With Double T — TT Pattern Mastery</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">With 6 T tiles in the bag — more than any other consonant except N — double-T draws happen often. The key is recognising TT patterns instantly: -UTTER, -ITTEN, -ATTLE, -OTTLE. BUTTERFLY leads at 17 points, while KITTEN, BUTTER, and BOTTLE offer reliable mid-range scoring when bingos aren't available.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">T Tiles in Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1pt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Per T Tile</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (BUTTERFLY)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TT Patterns</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Double-T Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 BUTTERFLY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 points · 9 letters · B(3)+U(1)+T(1)+T(1)+E(1)+R(1)+F(4)+L(1)+Y(4) · Bingo eligible</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 KITTEN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 points · 6 letters · K(5)+I(1)+T(1)+T(1)+E(1)+N(1) · K adds 5pts</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ BUTTER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 points · 6 letters · B(3)+U(1)+T(1)+T(1)+E(1)+R(1) · Common tiles</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ BOTTLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 points · 6 letters · B(3)+O(1)+T(1)+T(1)+L(1)+E(1) · Easy to draw</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">TT Pattern Recognition</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-UTTER family:</span> BUTTER, GUTTER, NUTTER, CUTTER, PUTTER, MUTTER. Six common words sharing one suffix — memorise the family and you'll spot plays instantly.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-ITTEN family:</span> KITTEN, MITTEN, BITTEN, SMITTEN. The K in KITTEN adds 5 bonus points. SMITTEN is 7 letters for a bingo. These are high-value patterns.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-ATTLE/-OTTLE:</span> BATTLE, RATTLE, CATTLE, BOTTLE, MOTTLE. These 6-letter words leave room for a front hook (S+BATTLE), building toward premium squares.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BUTTERFLY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KITTEN</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BUTTER</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOTTLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">T is the <span class="text-white font-medium">3rd most common tile</span> in the bag (6 copies). When you draw TT, think in patterns: -UTTER, -ITTEN, -ATTLE, -OTTLE. Each pattern family has 4-6 valid words, so you almost always have a play.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-double-t/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing Double T</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-words-with-double-letters/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Words With Double Letters</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-l/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With Double L</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all double-T words from your tiles — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
